    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5-10 min to prep, so get your slow cooker and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Turn on your <strong>slow cooker </strong>to high</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-spicy-korean-style-pork-and-leek-stew/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferable non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>diced pork </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until the pork is lightly browned</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-spicy-korean-style-pork-and-leek-stew/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, top, tail and chop your<strong> leek[s]</strong> into rounds and wash thoroughly to remove any grit</p><p>Top, tail and chop your <strong>carrot[s] </strong>into thick discs</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-spicy-korean-style-pork-and-leek-stew/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped leek</strong> to the dish with the<strong> chopped carrot </strong>and your<strong> baby button mushrooms</strong> and stir it all together</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-spicy-korean-style-pork-and-leek-stew/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>beef stock mix</strong>, <strong>gochujang paste </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!),<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> and <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong> to the stew<strong> </strong>with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-purple\"> [1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp] </span><strong>flour</strong></p><p>Add 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span><strong><span class=\"text-purple\"> </span>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-spicy-korean-style-pork-and-leek-stew/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once boiling, transfer everything from the pan to the <strong>slow cooker</strong></p><p>Give everything a good mix up, then cover and cook on high for 4 hours \u2013 this is your <strong>slow cooker spicy Korean-style pork & leek stew</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-spicy-korean-style-pork-and-leek-stew/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pork stew has 15 min left, add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/slow-cooker-spicy-korean-style-pork-and-leek-stew/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> slow cooker spicy Korean-style pork & leek stew</strong> with the <strong>cooked rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Season with <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Dig in!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
